        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Errol vows to raise the level of information&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 29-09-2000 at 17:00:41</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">Whats up with the Ninja-polls???</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			It seems that I have taken too many things for granted these past few weeks. <br><br>[no snide remarks, please ;-)]<br><br>Many burning issues have been debated in the Council, which have led to polls being posted on various subjects.<br><br>Some were self-evident, but other polls were simply posted too fast without corresponding in-depth information. This lead to confusion as to what the heck members were actually voting on, which benefits no one.<br><br>The Council is reading the messageboards several times a day and an Officer is almost always online, no matter what time-zone. That means that the Council has a very good grasp of all the issues currently being debated, both online and on the boards, but not everyone has that luxury.<br><br>I have taken steps to improve the level of information and I will make a news-item (on the frontpage) that corresponds with every new poll, that explains in detail what the poll is all about, so that members know what they vote on.<br><br>Sometimes though, a poll will be made that has no news-item attached to it - this could be small polls concerning Shadies pet or Nildars merchant-twin in Greater Fay, stuff like that...<br><br>And sometimes the poll will simply be blank. (like today).<br><br>I hope this will clear up any misunderstandings ;-)<br><br>- Errol
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
