            <br>
			Sir Lucan came, Sir Lucan fell. But he fell in two different places at once, leaving two corpses. Brother Jentry popped in the tunnel and died, yet still stood next to Sir Lucans corpse in the militia building. Sir Lucan was killed in the tunnel. And why can't any mages make pets in WFP?!?!?!?<br><br>Craziness abounds as the gods tested our mettle in more ways than one, but Garthazar, Aegis Lux, and friends stood strong against all odds, and the fifth Soulfire for Aegis Lux now burns brightly for master Garthazar.<br><br>A zone bug was preventing mage pets from being created, and it also caused Sir Lucans undead form to spawn as well, thus robbing us of the chance to kill and loot for the final piece to Soulfire. A quick petition to the gms brought positive results, and the zone was repopped 10 minutes later with assurances that it would work this time, which it did.<br><br>So now, with 5 Soulfires, 2 Ghoulbanes, and a great pack of yaulping paladins... Aegis Lux succeeds!
