          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Class News Bulletin - Rangers&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 12-09-2000 at 08:25:08</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">Rangers are being upgraded!</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			<b>Found on the offical Everquest Gameplay boards:</b><br><br><i>After a lot of internal testing, interacting with the community, and major debate, we've decided to upgrade Rangers as follows:<br> <br>We will be upping their dodge and parry to near Warrior levels. I don't want to get into specifics yet because we are still fine tuning, but the end result is that a Ranger should be significantly more survivable. <br><br>I'm personally happy with the solution because, rather than just increasing defense and making them more Warrior-like, we've upped skills that are more traditionally associated with Rangers (the view that they are nimble, chain-wearing fighters who often avoid attacks). <br><br>I'd also like to pre-announce a future goal and policy change: <br><br>Soon (we'll announce a date in the future), we're going to completely stop adjusting game balance as it relates to tweaking classes. Recently, we've made more changes than usual due to the level limits being raised from 50 to 60. Soon, however, we're going to come to a point where it stops. <br><br>We'll continue to add content (i.e. items, spells, etc.) and game balance will still be tweaked (and will continue to be tweaked as long as we do add content). But class balance changes as a whole will cease. <br><br>The Ranger upgrade is part of this. I'd say that hopefullly by early 2001 we'll be done. <br><br>Abashi or I will post more on this as we work out the plan in detail internally. <br><br>- Brad</i><br><br>This simply brings tears to my eyes... *sniff*<br><br>- Errol
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsEnd" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
		  Finally!!!!!
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
