            Aegis opens up for new Applicants again&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 10-09-2000 at 22:03:12</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">After a brief pause in the invitations, Aegis is now opening up for new applicants.</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			The new officers have been nominated. We are only waiting for the official inauguration to take place.<br><br>New rules for initiation has also been made.<br><br>Check them out in the Initiation section.<br><br>The main changes are:<br><br><b>1. Applicants must mail an application<br><br>2. Sponsors have been introduced.</b><br><br>The Applicants must now send an application to the e-mail adress <i>newapplicant@aegislux.dk</i>, stating why they wish to join us. This only applies to those who hasn't been recommended by a member of Aegis Lux.<br><br>Those regular members who recommends new applicants, will at the invitation of a new member be appointed Sponsor for the newcomer. This means that they will be held responsible for the honour and integrity of the new member during the reckoning period. <br><br>The Sponsor will then be called upon after the 14 days of reckoning to voice their oppinion regarding the eligibility of the Applicant.<br><br>Both changes should help the Council in their evaluation process of prospective 2nd. Circle members.<br><br>- Errol
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
