          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Should we change our logo?&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 10-09-2000 at 12:59:34</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">The result from the "Should we change our logo" poll is now in...</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			We decided to post this poll following posts on the Private Messageboard regarding that some felt the "Fairy" in the logo didn't represent the Guild in the true manner.<br><br>Well, the Council felt that a poll was in order, and here are the results summarized:<br><br><b>Should we change our logo?<br><br><i>Yes - 3 votes or 14 %<br><br>No - 14 votes or 67 %<br><br>I don't care - 4 votes or 19 %</i></b><br><br>The results are clear. The logo will not be changed.<br><br>But, let me urge you all to send in any suggestions to our mail adress (Fawna, Clarf or me). If you are skilled in the noble art of Graphics, send pictures of what you would like us to use instead. Although we love the "Fairy" image since it represents the "Out of this world" image we strive for in a Roleplaying guild, we are always open for suggestions. <br><br>Who knows...<br><br>But, until we see something that blows our mind, the Fairy stays ;-)
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
