            New Officers!&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 06-09-2000 at 09:28:35</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">New blood is needed in the Council...</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			The Council is in the process of nominating and discussing potential new candidates. The candidates will recieve a personal notification one of the following days.<br><br>When the new Council has been established, the Aegis will open up for new Applicants again. We are currently revising/adding to the existing initiation guidelines, since we feel a few more demands on new applicants are in order. What these new requirements will be, shall be revealed soon. Oh and don't worry, theres no new level cap ;-)<br><br>Basically we are trying to address the need to know more about new potential members who hasn't been recommended or aren't known by existing members. How do we determine if they're Aegis material?? We got a few tricks up our sleeves, which we think you'll like!<br><br>This should make sure Aegis Lux doesn't grow too fast or too big, but retains its "critical mass".<br><br>So, keep your eyes and ears peeled.<br><br>Hail Aegis Lux!
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
