      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Lanys T'vyl - Hate incarnate!&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 01-09-2000 at 19:45:59</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">Madrigan McBane stood face to face with the heinous daughter of Innoruuk in a GM event last night!</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			<i>"...Ever notice how certain events in yer life just leave their mark? Well let me tell ya laddies, very little compares to running face to face with the Lanys T'vyl, the Mistress of Hate herself! Aye, I did have the unfortunate run in with the wicked lass and I paid for it with my life. It seems that the Dark Elves' king has betrayed them. He has accused Lanys T'vyl of being a false prophet due to her defeat in Kithicor forest. This greatly angered Lanys and she is out to prove her superiority and status as the Daughter of Innorruuk by razing all the good cities of Norrath!<br><br>Yesterday around dusk I heard a great commotion coming from Nektulous Forest. When I looked up from my meditation I stood face to face with Lanys T'vyl! Behind her stood a small army of Teir' Dal of varying rank and distinction...but none eminated the Hate that came from this evil wench. She threw me an evil grin as she began some strange incantation, and my life was quickly vanquished. As my spirit travelled to Freeport I again encountered the Dark Elves shouting of "Burn the Human City to the ground!". Lanys then went on to take the lives of an Erudite, a Dwarf, a Human, a Barbarian (myself), a Halfling, a Wood Elf, and a High Elf! Finally, appeased, she retreated back to the realm of her father and left destruction in her wake...<br><br>War is on the horizon friends...are we prepared to stand and fight?! Let those who will stand behind the Shield of Light and we shall thwart her evil plan and rid Norrath of this evil menace once and for all!!"<br><br>On this 23rd day of June,<br><br>Madrigan MacBane</i><br><br>*ooc* this was a GM run event basically to further the story line for the Scars of Vellious expansion coming out soon. It was a very interesting event and I would advise all to expect some crazy things to happen in the next month or so concerning this issue. It was really cool to finally be a part of a GM event in person! <br>
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsEnd" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
		  The Shield of Light shall soon prove their worth. Brothers and Sisters, the time is near!
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
