            This should come as no surprise...&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 01-09-2000 at 10:12:34</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">The result of the "Which class do you find overpowered" poll is now in.</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			And it shouldn't come as a suprise, that our all-time favorite Shadowcloak, was voted most overpowered by a large majority:<br><br><i><b>Shadie: 26 votes or 50 %<br><br>Necros: 12 votes or 23 %<br><br>Pallys: 6 votes or 12 %<br><br>Druids: 6 votes or 12 %<br><br>Rangers: 1 votes or 2%<br><br>Enchanters: 1 vote or 2 %</i></b><br><br>Not a surprising poll, but two things did manage to lift my eyebrows a fraction.<br><br>First, a rather large part voted for Pallys being overpowered..Now where did that come from? Class envy from the druids??<br><br>And finally, Rangers and Enchanters <i>actually</i> recieved a vote! Now, I can personally strut around claiming that I am overpowered - a wish I have had from my first day in Surefall Glade.<br><br>I thank who ever gave my class that vote ;-)<br><br>Thanks buddy, I needed that!
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
